<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Northern Laos.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="73" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="72">The species was originally described from a single male. Here we recorded eight additional specimens from northern Laos (Fig. 20). The specimens with altitude data were collected between 1350-1900 m a.s.l.</paragraph>
<caption pageId="8" pageNumber="73">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="73">
<pageBreakToken pageId="8" pageNumber="73" start="start">Figure</pageBreakToken>
20. Distribution of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Polyphylla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyphylla (Granida)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Granida">Polyphylla (Granida)</taxonomicName>
species in continental Asia. Because of imprecise locality data, distributional mark of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Polyphylla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polyphylla (Granida) nikodymi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nikodymi" subGenus="Granida">Polyphylla (Granida) nikodymi</taxonomicName>
in Myanmar is omitted.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
